            <title>[KAFKA-13423] Error falsely reported on Kafka Streams app when GlobalKTables are used </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13423</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems that error of this form:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;ERROR streams.KafkaStreams: stream-client &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;testAppId-56832986-6ff0-4583-8aaf-85fafd7b4fe4&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Global thread has died. The streams application or client will now close to ERROR.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;are being reported when Streams are closed gracefully. This seems to be not right. See attached files for repro case&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

